{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_012SxDEkE7ntWekpp3QLJcG5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# cert-manager-operator — Agent Navigation Hub\n2\t\n3\tThe cert-manager Operator for OpenShift installs and manages three PKI-related\n4\toperands on behalf of cluster administrators: cert-manager (the core certificate\n5\tlifecycle controller, webhook, and cainjector), trust-manager (a cluster-wide CA\n6\tbundle distributor), and istio-csr (a gRPC bridge that allows Istio to request\n7\tcertificates from cert-manager). All operator machinery lives in the\n8\t`cert-manager-operator` namespace; all operands deploy into the `cert-manager`\n9\tnamespace (hardcoded). Each operand is governed by a cluster-scoped singleton\n10\tcustom resource (`CertManager/cluster`, `TrustManager/cluster`,\n11\t`IstioCSR/default`), and image references come exclusively from\n12\t`RELATED_IMAGE_*` environment variables injected by OLM.\n13\t\n14\t---\n15\t\n16\t## Component map\n17\t\n18\t| Component | Location | Role |\n19\t|---|---|---|\n20\t| API types | `api/operator/v1alpha1/` | CertManager, TrustManager, IstioCSR CRD structs + CEL validation |\n21\t| cert-manager controllers (library-go) | `pkg/controller/certmanager/` | Deploy/reconcile controller, webhook, cainjector using library-go hooks |\n22\t| TrustManager controller (controller-runtime) | `pkg/controller/trustmanager/` | Deploy trust-manager via SSA; manages CA bundle hash annotation |\n23\t| IstioCSR controller (controller-runtime) | `pkg/controller/istiocsr/` | Deploy istio-csr agent; manages per-namespace singleton |\n24\t| Embedded manifests (bindata) | `bindata/` + `pkg/operator/assets/` | Upstream YAML compiled into the binary via go-bindata |\n25\t| OptionalInformer / API discovery | `pkg/operator/utils/apidiscovery.go` | Detects absent OpenShift APIs (MicroShift compat) |\n26\t| Operator startup | `pkg/cmd/operator/cmd.go`, `pkg/operator/` | library-go `controllercmd` wiring, informer setup |\n27\t| Version/image metadata | `pkg/version/` | Embedded build-time version for status reporting |\n28\t\n29\t---\n30\t\n31\t## Key workflows\n32\t\n33\t### Add a new field to CertManager, TrustManager, or IstioCSR spec\n34\t\n35\t1. Edit the relevant `*_types.go` in `api/operator/v1alpha1/`.\n36\t2. Add kubebuilder marker comments (`+kubebuilder:validation:...`). For\n37\t   fields that must be immutable after first set, add a CEL rule:\n38\t   `+kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"oldSelf == '' || self == oldSelf\"`.\n39\t3. Run `make update` to regenerate CRD YAML and deepcopy functions.\n40\t4. Implement the spec field's effect in the matching controller:\n41\t   - **CertManager** → add a `DeploymentHookFunc` in\n42\t     `pkg/controller/certmanager/` and register it in\n43\t     `newGenericDeploymentController`.\n44\t   - **TrustManager/IstioCSR** → add a named mutation function and call it\n45\t     from `getDeploymentObject` (after `validateDeploymentManifest`).\n46\t5. Add unit tests in `*_test.go` alongside the new hook/function.\n47\t6. Update e2e tests under `test/e2e/` and verify with `make test-e2e`.\n48\t\n49\t### Add a new operand mutation function (TrustManager / IstioCSR path)\n50\t\n51\t1. Locate `pkg/controller/trustmanager/deployments.go` or\n52\t   `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`.\n53\t2. Write a new named function `updateXxx(deployment *appsv1.Deployment, ...) error`.\n54\t3. Call it from `getDeploymentObject`, **after** the\n55\t   `validateDeploymentManifest(deployment)` guard and in the intended application\n56\t   order (image override must come before resource overrides, etc.).\n57\t4. For cert-manager (library-go path): write a `DeploymentHookFunc` in\n58\t   `pkg/controller/certmanager/`, append it to the `hooks` slice inside\n59\t   `newGenericDeploymentController`. Hook ordering matters — break-glass\n60\t   `withUnsupportedArgsOverrideHook` must remain last.\n61\t5. Run `make test` to confirm existing tests still pass.\n62\t\n63\t### Add an optional informer for a new OpenShift API\n64\t\n65\t1. Define the GVR you need (group, version, resource string).\n66\t2. In `pkg/operator/` (near existing informer wiring), call:\n67\t   ```go\n68\t   myInformer, err := utils.InitInformerIfAvailable(\n69\t       utils.NewResourceDiscoverer(myGVR, discoveryClient),\n70\t       func() myapi.SharedInformerFactory { return myapi.NewSharedInformerFactory(...) },\n71\t   )\n72\t   ```\n73\t3. Pass `myInformer` to the controller constructor.\n74\t4. Inside the controller, guard every use with `myInformer.Applicable()`.\n75\t   When false the controller must degrade gracefully (no-op, not error).\n76\t5. The discoverer treats API-not-found as `(false, nil)`, so MicroShift and\n77\t   vanilla Kubernetes clusters continue to work without the API group.\n78\t\n79\t---\n80\t\n81\t## Troubleshooting quick-reference\n82\t\n83\t| Symptom | One-line solution |\n84\t|---|---|\n85\t| Operator loop-crashes with \"invalid trust-manager deployment manifest\" | The embedded bindata YAML fails `validateDeploymentManifest`; run `make update` and ensure `bindata/trust-manager/` matches the expected schema |\n86\t| Operand pod not restarting after CA bundle ConfigMap update | Check that the SHA-256 annotation (`cert-manager.io/ca-bundle-hash`) on the pod template was updated; the hash covers PEM content, not `resourceVersion` |\n87\t| Immutable field rejection at admission (CEL error) | Attempt to change a `XValidation`-guarded field; delete and recreate the CR, or accept the current value |\n88\t| `RELATED_IMAGE_CERT_MANAGER_*` not found, pod uses wrong image | OLM env injection missing; verify the CSV `relatedImages` section and that the operator pod env vars are set |\n89\t| IstioCSR controller does nothing | Feature gate `IstioCSR=true` must be passed via `--unsupported-addon-features` flag; it is off by default |\n90\t\n91\t---\n92\t\n93\t## Further reading\n94\t\n95\t- [agentic/DESIGN.md](agentic/DESIGN.md) — architecture decisions and reconciliation flow\n96\t- [agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md](agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md) — local dev setup, make targets\n97\t- [agentic/TESTING.md](agentic/TESTING.md) — unit, e2e, and coverage guidance\n98\t- [agentic/RELIABILITY.md](agentic/RELIABILITY.md) — status conditions, degraded handling\n99\t- [agentic/SECURITY.md](agentic/SECURITY.md) — CEL policies, network policies, RBAC\n100\t\n101\t### Component deep-dives\n102\t\n103\t- [TrustManager controller](agentic/design-docs/components/trustmanager-controller.md)\n104\t- [IstioCSR controller](agentic/design-docs/components/istiocsr-controller.md)\n105\t- [OptionalInformer](agentic/design-docs/components/optional-informer.md)\n106\t\n107\t### Concepts\n108\t\n109\t- [Singleton pattern](agentic/domain/concepts/singleton-pattern.md)\n110\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"938f6b2d-d7c1-48fc-8ccf-bdceaece26d9","uuid":"f0f84907-f5ff-4771-b761-c727d2b8afb0","timestamp":"2026-07-20T16:53:03.026Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/cert-manager-operator-treatment/AGENTS.md","content":"# cert-manager-operator — Agent Navigation Hub\n\nThe cert-manager Operator for OpenShift installs and manages three PKI-related\noperands on behalf of cluster administrators: cert-manager (the core certificate\nlifecycle controller, webhook, and cainjector), trust-manager (a cluster-wide CA\nbundle distributor), and istio-csr (a gRPC bridge that allows Istio to request\ncertificates from cert-manager). All operator machinery lives in the\n`cert-manager-operator` namespace; all operands deploy into the `cert-manager`\nnamespace (hardcoded). Each operand is governed by a cluster-scoped singleton\ncustom resource (`CertManager/cluster`, `TrustManager/cluster`,\n`IstioCSR/default`), and image references come exclusively from\n`RELATED_IMAGE_*` environment variables injected by OLM.\n\n---\n\n## Component map\n\n| Component | Location | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| API types | `api/operator/v1alpha1/` | CertManager, TrustManager, IstioCSR CRD structs + CEL validation |\n| cert-manager controllers (library-go) | `pkg/controller/certmanager/` | Deploy/reconcile controller, webhook, cainjector using library-go hooks |\n| TrustManager controller (controller-runtime) | `pkg/controller/trustmanager/` | Deploy trust-manager via SSA; manages CA bundle hash annotation |\n| IstioCSR controller (controller-runtime) | `pkg/controller/istiocsr/` | Deploy istio-csr agent; manages per-namespace singleton |\n| Embedded manifests (bindata) | `bindata/` + `pkg/operator/assets/` | Upstream YAML compiled into the binary via go-bindata |\n| OptionalInformer / API discovery | `pkg/operator/utils/apidiscovery.go` | Detects absent OpenShift APIs (MicroShift compat) |\n| Operator startup | `pkg/cmd/operator/cmd.go`, `pkg/operator/` | library-go `controllercmd` wiring, informer setup |\n| Version/image metadata | `pkg/version/` | Embedded build-time version for status reporting |\n\n---\n\n## Key workflows\n\n### Add a new field to CertManager, TrustManager, or IstioCSR spec\n\n1. Edit the relevant `*_types.go` in `api/operator/v1alpha1/`.\n2. Add kubebuilder marker comments (`+kubebuilder:validation:...`). For\n   fields that must be immutable after first set, add a CEL rule:\n   `+kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"oldSelf == '' || self == oldSelf\"`.\n3. Run `make update` to regenerate CRD YAML and deepcopy functions.\n4. Implement the spec field's effect in the matching controller:\n   - **CertManager** → add a `DeploymentHookFunc` in\n     `pkg/controller/certmanager/` and register it in\n     `newGenericDeploymentController`.\n   - **TrustManager/IstioCSR** → add a named mutation function and call it\n     from `getDeploymentObject` (after `validateDeploymentManifest`).\n5. Add unit tests in `*_test.go` alongside the new hook/function.\n6. Update e2e tests under `test/e2e/` and verify with `make test-e2e`.\n\n### Add a new operand mutation function (TrustManager / IstioCSR path)\n\n1. Locate `pkg/controller/trustmanager/deployments.go` or\n   `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`.\n2. Write a new named function `updateXxx(deployment *appsv1.Deployment, ...) error`.\n3. Call it from `getDeploymentObject`, **after** the\n   `validateDeploymentManifest(deployment)` guard and in the intended application\n   order (image override must come before resource overrides, etc.).\n4. For cert-manager (library-go path): write a `DeploymentHookFunc` in\n   `pkg/controller/certmanager/`, append it to the `hooks` slice inside\n   `newGenericDeploymentController`. Hook ordering matters — break-glass\n   `withUnsupportedArgsOverrideHook` must remain last.\n5. Run `make test` to confirm existing tests still pass.\n\n### Add an optional informer for a new OpenShift API\n\n1. Define the GVR you need (group, version, resource string).\n2. In `pkg/operator/` (near existing informer wiring), call:\n   ```go\n   myInformer, err := utils.InitInformerIfAvailable(\n       utils.NewResourceDiscoverer(myGVR, discoveryClient),\n       func() myapi.SharedInformerFactory { return myapi.NewSharedInformerFactory(...) },\n   )\n   ```\n3. Pass `myInformer` to the controller constructor.\n4. Inside the controller, guard every use with `myInformer.Applicable()`.\n   When false the controller must degrade gracefully (no-op, not error).\n5. The discoverer treats API-not-found as `(false, nil)`, so MicroShift and\n   vanilla Kubernetes clusters continue to work without the API group.\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting quick-reference\n\n| Symptom | One-line solution |\n|---|---|\n| Operator loop-crashes with \"invalid trust-manager deployment manifest\" | The embedded bindata YAML fails `validateDeploymentManifest`; run `make update` and ensure `bindata/trust-manager/` matches the expected schema |\n| Operand pod not restarting after CA bundle ConfigMap update | Check that the SHA-256 annotation (`cert-manager.io/ca-bundle-hash`) on the pod template was updated; the hash covers PEM content, not `resourceVersion` |\n| Immutable field rejection at admission (CEL error) | Attempt to change a `XValidation`-guarded field; delete and recreate the CR, or accept the current value |\n| `RELATED_IMAGE_CERT_MANAGER_*` not found, pod uses wrong image | OLM env injection missing; verify the CSV `relatedImages` section and that the operator pod env vars are set |\n| IstioCSR controller does nothing | Feature gate `IstioCSR=true` must be passed via `--unsupported-addon-features` flag; it is off by default |\n\n---\n\n## Further reading\n\n- [agentic/DESIGN.md](agentic/DESIGN.md) — architecture decisions and reconciliation flow\n- [agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md](agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md) — local dev setup, make targets\n- [agentic/TESTING.md](agentic/TESTING.md) — unit, e2e, and coverage guidance\n- [agentic/RELIABILITY.md](agentic/RELIABILITY.md) — status conditions, degraded handling\n- [agentic/SECURITY.md](agentic/SECURITY.md) — CEL policies, network policies, RBAC\n\n### Component deep-dives\n\n- [TrustManager controller](agentic/design-docs/components/trustmanager-controller.md)\n- [IstioCSR controller](agentic/design-docs/components/istiocsr-controller.md)\n- [OptionalInformer](agentic/design-docs/components/optional-informer.md)\n\n### Concepts\n\n- [Singleton pattern](agentic/domain/concepts/singleton-pattern.md)\n","numLines":110,"startLine":1,"totalLines":110}}}
